HEADWORD: Solarization
<hw>So`lar*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>Injury of a photographic picture caused by
exposing it for too long a time to the sun's light in the camera;
burning; excessive insolation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solarize</ent>⟦br⟧
